class Solution {
    public boolean canIWin(int maxChoosableInteger, int desiredTotal) {
        int maxNum = (maxChoosableInteger * (desiredTotal + 1));
        return maxNum <= desiredTotal;
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution checks if the maximum number of choosable integers multiplied by the desired total is less than or equal to the desired total. If it is, the first player can force a win by choosing the maximum number of choosable integers and not allowing the second player to choose any number. Otherwise, the second player has a chance to win. The time complexity is O(1) since the algorithm only makes a single comparison, and the space complexity is O(1) as well, as the algorithm uses a constant amount of space. The energy implications are low because the algorithm does not involve any resource-intensive operations.

